1) Modulus of negative number:
1-A) -60 % 9 = -60 -(-63) = 3 since -63 = 9 * -7 and remainder is 3 since modulus ( % ) value can never be negative
1-B) -40 % 7 = -40 -(-42) = 2 since -42 = 7 * -6 and remainder is 2 since modulus ( % ) value can never be negative

2) The value of a % m will always be in the range of [0, m-1]

3) Modulus Operation Formulas:

3-A) (a + b) % M = (a % M + b % M) % M --> Modular Arithmetic Rule
3-B) (a * b) % M = (a % M * b % M) % M --> Modular Multiplicative Rule
